# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

This project was scaffolded by `arc init`.

## What You Get

- `policy.yaml`: a minimal ARC policy that grants one governed tool call
- `src/bin/hello_server.rs`: a tiny MCP tool server stub
- `src/bin/demo.rs`: a smoke runner that launches `arc mcp serve`, calls the
  governed tool, and prints the resulting receipt line

## Run It

1. Build the scaffold:

   ```bash
   cargo build
   ```

2. Point the demo at an `arc` binary if it is not already on your `PATH`:

   ```bash
   ARC_BIN=/path/to/arc cargo run --quiet --bin demo
   ```

3. The demo writes the local receipt store under `.arc/receipts.db` and prints
   the latest receipt after the governed tool call succeeds.

## Customize It

- Rename `hello_world` in `src/bin/hello_server.rs` to your first tool
- Tighten `policy.yaml` to the exact server, tool, and budget envelope you need
- Extend `demo.rs` into your own client or replace it with a framework SDK in
  later phases
